name: ferredoxin---NAD+ reductase
names: NADH-ferredoxin NAP reductase (component of naphthalene dioxygenase multicomponent enzyme system)
NADH-ferredoxin TOL reductase (component of toluene dioxygenase)
classes: Acting on iron-sulfur proteins as donors;
With NAD+ or NADP+ as acceptor
reaction: (1) 2 reduced [2Fe-2S] ferredoxin + NAD+ + H+ = 2 oxidized [2Fe-2S] ferredoxin + NADH [RN:R05875]; (2) reduced 2[4Fe-4S] ferredoxin + NAD+ + H+ = oxidized 2[4Fe-4S] ferredoxin + NADH
comment: Contains FAD. Reaction (1) is written for a [2Fe-2S] ferredoxin, which is characteristic of some mono- and dioxygenase systems. The alternative reaction (2) is written for a 2[4Fe-4S] ferredoxin, which transfers two electrons, and occurs in metabolism of anaerobic bacteria.
